# Content Channel Strategy

Before creating, editing, reviewing, or restructuring articles, follow:

- `AGENTS.md`
- `docs/content-channel-strategy.md`

## Shared positioning

Use this positioning consistently across note, Zenn, Qiita, Growth Lab, and GitHub:

> AIコーディングをチーム開発に乗せる運用設計

## Channel roles

- note: background, narrative, management perspective, and team-operation lessons.
- Zenn: technical deep dives, implementation details, schemas, GitHub Actions, and examples.
- Qiita: search-entry articles, short how-to notes, troubleshooting, and first-step guides.
- Growth Lab: canonical long-form guides, validation logs, and evergreen documentation.
- GitHub: OSS source of truth, README, releases, issues, and implementation docs.

## Editing rules

- Decide the destination channel before rewriting.
- Match article depth and tone to the channel role.
- Do not duplicate the same body across platforms.
- Use contextual cross-links when useful.
- Prefer concrete pain, concrete workflow, and concrete next action.
- Connect changes to PlanGate, River Reviewer, Agent Skills, AI-readable repository design, or Metrics and governance when relevant.
